article.description: — PJ Pipes had 19 points as Santa Clara edged past Loyola Marymount 84-80 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Pipes lifts Santa Clara over Loyola Marymount 84-80
article.linkText: Pipes lifts Santa Clara over Loyola Marymount 84-80
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- — PJ Pipes had 19 points as Santa Clara edged past Loyola Marymount 84-80 on Thursday night. Josip Vrankic added 18 points for the Broncos, while Keshawn Justice chipped in 16. Jalen Williams had 11 points and three blocks for Santa Clara (18-9, 8-4 West Coast Conference). Eli Scott had 30 points for the Lions (9-15, 2-10), who have now lost eight games in a row. Cam Shelton added 14 points. Joe Quintana had 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
